ğŸ“– **Description:**
    The `msgmerge` command is used to merge translated message files (.po) with the original template files (.pot). This command helps you update your translations with the latest changes in the source text. If the source text has changed, `msgmerge` identifies the new or modified strings in the translation file, allowing you to translate them.

âš™ï¸ **Options:**
    ğŸ”¹ `msgmerge -o output.po input.po template.pot`  --> ğŸ“¤ Creates a new translated file (output.po) using the old translated file (input.po) and the template (.pot).
    ğŸ”¹ `msgmerge --update input.po template.pot`  --> ğŸ”„ Updates the translated file (input.po) in place.
    ğŸ”¹ `msgmerge --backup=numbered ...` --> ğŸ’¾ Creates a numbered backup of the original translation file before updating.
    ğŸ”¹ `msgmerge -n input.po template.pot` --> ğŸ“ Removes obsolete translated entries (those no longer present in the template file).

ğŸ›  **Examples:**

    $ msgmerge -o french.po french.po.old app.pot

    ğŸ”¹ Merges `french.po.old` with `app.pot` and saves the result in `french.po`.

    $ msgmerge --update french.po app.pot

    ğŸ”¹ Updates `french.po` with changes from `app.pot`.

âœ… **Simple Example:**

    $ msgmerge --update en.po app.pot
